# Boyle — Project Context

## Overview

Boyle is a **BSD 3-Clause** high-performance **C++23** mathematical library (with **GNU extensions**) for autonomous driving and robotics: dense/sparse linear algebra, curves, convex optimization, and kinetics. **Python** support is planned; prefer **uv** + **ruff** + **pyright** when Python code exists.

## Technical Requirements

| Area | Requirement |
| ---- | ----------- |
| C++ standard | C++23 |
| CMake | 3.31+ |
| Generators | Ninja (CMake), xmake optional |
| Format (C++) | clang-format 20+, Microsoft-based style |
| Lint (C++) | clang-tidy 20+ |
| Format / lint (Python) | ruff, pyright |
| Tests (C++) | doctest 2.4.12 |
| Tests (Python) | pytest via `uv run pytest` |
| License | BSD 3-Clause |

## Namespace Structure

| Namespace | Purpose |
| --------- | ------- |
| `boyle` | Root |
| `boyle::common` | Shared utilities, macros, logging |
| `boyle::math` | Core math |
| `boyle::math::pmr` | PMR allocator variants |
| `boyle::math::detail` | Private implementation |
| `boyle::cvxopm` | Convex optimization |
| `boyle::kinetics` | Motion models |

## Module Dependency Graph

`common` → `math` → `cvxopm` → `kinetics` (acyclic).

## Third-Party Dependencies (typical)

| Library | Role |
| ------- | ---- |
| Boost | Serialization, unordered containers |
| doctest | Unit tests |
| spdlog | Logging |
| OSQP / qdldl | QP solvers |
| OpenBLAS | BLAS/LAPACK |
| cxxopts, Matplot++ | Test drivers / plots |

Exact versions are pinned via **CPM** / **vcpkg** / **xmake** recipes—follow existing `cmake/` and `xmake/` patterns.

## Common Macros

Defined in `boyle/common/utils/macros.hpp` (names may vary slightly—follow tree):

- `ENABLE_COPY` / `DISABLE_COPY`, `ENABLE_MOVE` / `DISABLE_MOVE`, `ENABLE_COPY_AND_MOVE` / `DISABLE_COPY_AND_MOVE`
- `ENABLE_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS` / `DISABLE_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS`
- `MAKE_SINGLETON`
- `BOYLE_CHECK_PARAMS` — when enabled, validate indices/params (often throws `std::out_of_range`); not a status type

## Concepts & Type Aliases

- Prefer **C++20 concepts** for template constraints (`ScalarArithmetic`, iterators, etc.).
- **Type-alias suffixes**: `s` = float, `d` = double, `c` = `std::complex<float>`, `z` = `std::complex<double>` (e.g. `Vec2s`, `Vec3d`).

## Build Commands (CMake)

```bash
cmake --preset linux-gcc-x64
cmake --build --preset linux-gcc-x64
ctest --preset linux-gcc-x64
ctest --preset linux-gcc-x64 -R <regex>
```

Other presets: `linux-clang-x64`, `darwin-gcc-arm64`, `darwin-clang-arm64`, `windows-msvc-x64`. Binary dir: `out/build/<preset>` (see `CMakePresets.json`).

## Build Commands (xmake)

```bash
xmake config -m release
xmake build
xmake run <target>
```

## Build Configuration Options (CMake cache)

| Option | Typical role |
| ------ | ------------- |
| `BOYLE_CHECK_PARAMS` | Extra parameter checks (`ON`/`OFF`) |
| `BOYLE_BUILD_TESTING` | Build tests |
| `BOYLE_ENABLE_INSTALL` | Install rules |
| `BOYLE_USE_BLAS_LAPACK` | BLAS/LAPACK backend selection |
| `BOYLE_USE_BOOST_UNORDERED` | Boost unordered containers |
| `BOYLE_USE_SIMD` | SIMD kernels |

## CMake Helper Functions (`cmake/utils.cmake`)

| Function | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| `boyle_cxx_library(NAME ... HDRS ... SRCS ... DEPS ...)` | Header-only or compiled library targets; exposes `boyle::<NAME>` alias |
| `boyle_cxx_module(NAME ... IXXS ... SRCS ... DEPS ...)` | C++20 modules (`.ixx`), when used |
| `boyle_cxx_test(NAME ... SRCS ... DEPS ...)` | doctest executable + `add_test` |

**Keywords**: `PUBLIC`, `TESTONLY`, `DISABLE_INSTALL`, plus `COPTS`, `DEFINES`, `LINKOPTS` as needed.

## Coding Standards (pointers)

- **Trailing return types** are **mandatory** on new functions: `auto foo() -> void;`
- **Microsoft-oriented** naming: `camelCase` functions, `m_` private members, `PascalCase` types
- **Exceptions** for errors; use `BOYLE_CHECK_PARAMS` guards where applicable—not status objects
- See `.cursor/rules/cpp/cpp-coding-standards.mdc` and `.github/instructions/` for detail
